Metadata: California Sea Grant Fisheries Newsletter (Winter, Spring, Summer, and Fall 2004)
University of California Sea Grant Extension Program
Document type code changed from CUIMR to CASG with the Summer 2004 issue onward. The Summer and Fall issue are numbered as: CASG-N-04-011

This quarterly publication of the California Sea Grant Extension Program and the UC Division of Agriculture and Natural Resources focuses on marine fisheries, seafood, and coastal issues. Main articles include: Dungeness crab tagging project; Comparing SCUBA and fishing surveys: collaboration between fishermen, CDFG, and university scientists, by R. Starr; Japanese IIFET fisheries meetings; Historical ecology: Oral histories of retired Morro Bay commercial fishermen.
